                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d870">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.5561/77a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-20T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 20, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1303. Your 1959, November 21, 5 p.m. The Navy Department desires to assign
                    Lieutenant C. H. Taecker as Assistant Naval Attaché or Naval Observer at the
                    Port of Vladivostok. Upon our suggestion the Navy has agreed to assign Taecker
                    as Assistant Naval Attaché to the Embassy at Kuibyshev with the understanding
                    that he will be temporarily detailed to Vladivostok.</p>
                <p>It would be appreciated if you would secure the approval of the Soviet
                    Government.</p>
                <p>No announcement will be made here that he is going to or will be stationed at
                    Vladivostok.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
